# Next.js 16+ Conventions

## Server vs Client Components

- **Default to Server Components** -- use `'use client'` only when needed (hooks, events, browser APIs)
- Server Components for data fetching, backend resource access, sensitive information
- Client Components only for event listeners, React hooks, browser APIs, interactive elements

## App Router Patterns

- Use `proxy.ts` instead of `middleware.ts` (deprecated in Next.js 16)
- `params` and `searchParams` are async -- always `await` them
- Async request APIs: `cookies()`, `headers()`, `draftMode()` must be awaited

## Caching

- Use `'use cache'` directive with `cacheLife()` for component-level caching
- Use `updateTag()` for immediate cache invalidation
- Use `revalidateTag()` for stale-while-revalidate
- Use `refresh()` for non-cached data refresh

## Data Fetching

- Direct database/API access in Server Components without client-side fetching
- Use `Promise.all()` for parallel independent queries -- avoid waterfalls
- Use Prisma `include` to fetch relations in a single query instead of N+1
- Add `error.tsx` for graceful error handling per route

## Server Actions

- Always validate inputs with Zod in Server Actions
- Always check session/user authentication before mutations
- Use `revalidatePath()` or `revalidateTag()` after mutations
- Use `useFormState` and `useFormStatus` for progressive enhancement

## Performance

- Stream slow components with `<Suspense>` for better TTFB
- Use `next/image` with `priority` for above-the-fold images
- Enable React Compiler (`reactCompiler: true` in next.config.ts) for automatic memoization
- Use dynamic imports for heavy client-only components

## Project Structure

```
app/
  (auth)/           # Route group for auth pages
  (dashboard)/      # Route group for dashboard
  api/              # API routes
  actions/          # Server Actions
components/
  ui/               # shadcn/ui components
  forms/            # Form components
  providers/        # Context providers
lib/
  db.ts             # Database client
  auth.ts           # Auth utilities
  validations/      # Zod schemas
```

## Type Safety

- Validate environment variables at startup with Zod
- Type Server Action inputs and outputs
- Use Prisma-generated types for database models
- All files should be `.ts`/`.tsx`
